# Agent Registry

Compact operator matrix for GrooveGraph Next. Agent role cards live under **`.cursor/agents/*.mdc`**; rules under **`.cursor/rules/{global,engineering}/`**; skills under **`.cursor/skills/**/**/SKILL.md`**.

- Prefer the listed **specialist** when the task fits one domain.
- Use **`orchestrator`** when routing is unclear or work spans multiple domains.
- Use **`architecture`** before changing contracts across UI, API, graph, or LLM layers.
- Default agent **`model`** in frontmatter is **`inherit`** (follows parent session) unless a card pins a model.
- Keep handoffs explicit; see **`docs/CONTEXT_PACKETS.mdc`**.

| Agent | Use for | Default model (frontmatter) |
|---|---|---|
| `orchestrator` | Decomposition, routing, handoffs, final synthesis | `inherit` |
| `architecture` | Structure, contracts, boundaries, tradeoffs (often read-first) | `inherit` |
| `development` | Cross-cutting implementation, glue, debugging | `inherit` |
| `api` | Endpoints, validation, typed API contracts | `inherit` |
| `ui` | Client UI, layout, components, CSS | `inherit` |
| `design` | Design system, tokens, Figma/Pencil alignment | `inherit` |
| `graph` | TypeDB schema, queries, graph persistence mapping | `inherit` |
| `llm` | Prompts, context packing, structured model I/O | `inherit` |
| `qa` | Test plans, regression, e2e scenarios (often read-first) | `inherit` |
| `devops` | Deploy, env, pipelines, cloud ops (may be long-running) | `inherit` |

**Hygiene and cleanup:** follow **`docs/HYGIENE.mdc`**; primary implementer is typically **`development`** with **`qa`** for validation—there is no separate `hygienist` agent file.

**Meta authoring (rules/skills):** owned by **`development`** with **`architecture`** review when contracts change; there is no separate `composer-meta` agent file.
